Today we did the math and realized that we have been friends for 18 years! One of my favorite memories was Valentine’s Day 2007. We went to see Music and Lyrics together and Brooke professed her love for me. We were married for ten years after that. The marriage had many ups and downs. I was gay for most of it. Glad we’ve remained friends!!!!
Went to Adeline’s 2nd birthday party and didn’t freak out when she got more attention than me all afternoon. It was hard, but I persevered!!!!

It is through tears and a shattered heart that I announce my mom’s passing. She was my best friend and my biggest supporter, and I feel lost knowing that I can no longer call her on a daily basis to talk about everything and nothing. I am devastated, but I also know that she is now at peace, which is what is important. She was loved by many and she had so much love to give, especially to animals. Her dogs were her everything. My world is emptier but my heart is filled with a lifetime of memories that will never diminish. I love you, mom. 🩵

This was my mom’s favorite photo of me. She titled it “The Mess™️.” She ran upstairs to do something (I want to say shower or color her hair but I don’t remember) and she told me to be good. When she came downstairs to this she was so gobsmacked at the audacity of it that all she could do was laugh. It’s also proof that I’ve always been…me. Hope this makes you smile now that you’re at peace, mom. I love you and I miss you so much. 🩵🩵
Went to a place my mom loved (the Chili’s in my hometown) with some people I love. A moment of happiness and laughter that was much needed. 🩵
My arch-nemesis got married last night, but I didn’t go to celebrate her and her love. I went to remind her that I am always one step ahead of her. Watching. Waiting. Ready to get my revenge.
Anything for my hungry guys!

5 years ago, Brenden (an acquaintance at the time who I always enjoyed seeing out and about) convinced me to join a bowling league with him and the rest is history. It’s fitting that we celebrated his 30th birthday doing what sparked our friendship. I am so darn thankful he took that first step towards making us better friends, because he is a GEM and I now can’t imagine my life without him. We see like 2-3 movies a week together and eat at Panda Express and Chili’s way more than I’m comfortable admitting, and these moments are always the highlights of my week. Happy 30th, Brenden!!!
